        <span class="news"> </span><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Text" --> 
              
              <p align="right" class="headlines"><br>
                SYSPRO Releases “Out-of-the-Box” Web Services<span class="news"> <br>
                <font color="#FFFFFF"> <img src="../../Images/clear.gif" hspace="5" vspace="5" align="right"> 
                </font> 
                <br>
                </span><span class="headlinebody">November 18, 2002 – SYSPRO has announced the release of a series of business objects that enable SYSPRO customers to speed the development of a wide variety of Web Services.  The “business objects” are COM “building blocks” that allow customers using SYSPRO e.net solutions and Microsoft architecture to easily and quickly build and customize a wide variety of Web Services.  For example, the business objects facilitate the rapid development of Web Services that provide a variety of real-time insight into such areas as supplier inventories, factory floor conditions, order status, and more. <BR>
<BR>
“We’ve reached the stage where customers no longer have to live within the confines of the system.  SYSPRO business objects allow customers to ‘think out of the box,’” said Joey Benadretti, SYSPRO vice president.<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO e.net solutions is one of the first products on the market to leverage the Microsoft .NET framework and the XML standard.  SYSPRO e.net solutions is the foundation of SYSPRO 6.0 software and a new generation of “customizable” Web-based applications/services.  SYSPRO e.net solutions is a component-based architecture designed to provide a highly cost-effective way for SYSPRO customers to integrate best-of-breed applications, maximize business-to-business trading and leverage wireless connectivity.   <BR>
<BR>
Among the Web Services business objects being announced today by SYSPRO are those pertaining to financial, multi-mode manufacturing and distribution operations.  According to Benadretti, “Many COM objects, such as Available to Promise Query, Bill of Materials Costing Query and Goods In Transit Inventory Transfers, are indicative of the value-add that SYSPRO continually delivers to customers.”<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO currently has customers using its Web Services, and Benadretti notes that the company has been saturated with interest from prospects and customers on the use of Web Services. <BR>
<BR>
As well as ushering in a new generation of Web Services, SYSPRO 6.0 enterprise software offers major new additions such as Business Analytics, Document Flow Management, integrated CRM and more powerful Finite Scheduling forming part of an integrated APS.  <BR>
<BR>
Business Analytics enables users to create multi-dimensional views of their financial and operational data, enabling officers to make more efficient decisions based upon superior insight into business conditions.   It includes a series of data mining cubes to produce dynamic, general and enterprise specific metrics, ratios and analyses.  An administrator toolset allows for the manipulation of the cube(s) to suit customer requirements without any special On-line Analytical Processing (OLAP) knowledge. <BR>
<BR>
The Document Flow Manager facilitates supply chain communications, enabling a company to automate business processes and build communication infrastructures that facilitate seamless collaborative commerce.  The Document Flow Manager automates the flow of business transactions as they electronically arrive at a company in a XML document format.  Inbound and outbound transactions can be tracked and posted directly and automatically into and from the ERP system.<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO CRM closes the gap between the front office and the back office by integrating all activities without duplicating input.  With SYSPRO CRM sales, marketing and customer support operations work collaboratively to achieve total customer satisfaction.  SYSPRO CRM offers powerful synchronization features and web tools to facilitate remote and off-line access via browser, laptop and web-enabled portable or handheld PDA devices.<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO 6.0 APS is aimed at improving lead times, increasing production flexibility, reducing inventory levels and increasing throughput.  SYSPRO APS consists of four modules:  Finite Capacity Scheduling, Factory Planning, Progress Tracking and Quality Monitoring.  <BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO 6.0 software features enhancements in almost all existing modules.  For example, the Quotations Module incorporates the hierarchical requirements for Projects and Contracts.  The functionality in the Product Configurator has been extended; the Point of Sale entry has been enhanced with a more efficient means of accepting payment/deposits against normal orders; drill-down capability has been improved in a number of areas with increased security and visibility throughout the product.<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO is a world leader in providing manufacturing, distribution and financial accounting software solutions with thousands of installations in more than 50 countries.  SYSPRO is one of the world’s most honored software companies. Recent milestones include: The premier K2 Quality Award for “Installation Channel/Methodology” for the SYSPRO STARS Implementation Methodology; Voted Number One in 2002 Middle Market ERP Software Survey Conducted by Accounting Research; Recipient of START Magazine’s First Annual Vision Award (2001) and “Hottest Company” designation for three years; Finalist for Developer of the Year (2002) by Software Council of Southern California; Ranked Among World’s Top Software Companies by MSI Magazine, Managing Automation Magazine, Logistics Management Magazine and Software Magazine; and Given Highest Ratings in Accounting and Manufacturing Software Reviews by CPA Software News for ten consecutive years.<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO software is marketed worldwide through offices in the U.S., Canada, Africa, Australia and the U.K.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
SYSPRO is exhibiting at COMDEX, Las Vegas, in Booth 10858.</span></p>
